  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "56\n21\n\nWill Durant on HO LOGOS:\n\nTo create the world by giving form to matter, and to establish relations with man, God used a host of intermediary beings, called angels by the Jews, daimones by the Greeks, and Ideas by Plato. These, say Philo, may popularly be conceived as persons, though really they exist only in the Divine Mind, as thoughts and powers of God. Together these powers constitute what the Stoics called the Logos, or Divine Reason creating and guiding the world. Fluctuating between",
      "matched_alias": "Durant",
